  "texts": [
    "The world-volume of O 3 also contains topological surface operators, but in this special class of 3-charges, all such surface operators can be constructed by gauging/condensing the topological line operators in B along two-dimension sub-world-volumes of O 3.",
    "Mathematically, the topological surfaces and lines combine together to form a fusion 2category denoted by Mod(B), (104) whose objects are module categories of B.",
    "Figure 14:14Figure 14: The action of h 1, h 2 ∈ H L L ′ on a non-genuine local operator O.",
    "Depending on whether we fuse first and then act, or first act and then fuse, we generate two different situations, shown at the bottom-left and bottom-right of the figure.",
    "A chain of equalities equates the two, leading to the equation (114)."
